# MDEdit Phoenix Project Structure

This is a Phoenix 1.8 web application for collaborative markdown editing with real-time features.

## Key Files and Structure

- **Main Application**: [lib/mdedit.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit.ex) - Main application module
- **Web Module**: [lib/mdedit_web.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit_web.ex) - Web application configuration with imports and aliases
- **Router**: [lib/mdedit_web/router.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit_web/router.ex) - Route definitions for the application
- **Core Components**: [lib/mdedit_web/components/core_components.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit_web/components/core_components.ex) - Reusable UI components including flash messages
- **Main LiveViews**:
  - [lib/mdedit_web/live/home_live.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit_web/live/home_live.ex) - Home page
  - [lib/mdedit_web/live/editor_live.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit_web/live/editor_live.ex) - Main collaborative markdown editor
- **Business Logic**:
  - [lib/mdedit/documents.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit/documents.ex) - Documents context
  - [lib/mdedit/documents/document.ex](mdc:lib/mdedit/documents/document.ex) - Document schema with admin tokens and expiration
- **Assets**: [assets/js/app.js](mdc:assets/js/app.js) - JavaScript with LiveView hooks and localStorage management
- **Configuration**: [mix.exs](mdc:mix.exs) - Project dependencies and configuration

## Key Features

- Real-time collaborative markdown editing
- Etherpad-style access control (creator admin tokens, share via link)
- Document expiration (1 day, 1 week, 1 month, 1 year)
- Auto-save functionality
- Mobile-responsive tabbed interface
- User presence tracking
- No public document discovery (private by default)

## Development Commands

- `mix phx.server` - Start development server
- `mix precommit` - Run pre-commit checks and fix issues
- `mix compile` - Compile the application
- `mix test` - Run tests